CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets.
CSS is enhances the appearance of the web page by applying styles to the HTML elements.
Cascading Style Sheets are an important way to control how your web pages look.
CSS is used to define styles for your web pages, including the design, layout and variations in display for different devices and screen sizes.
CSS it is not a programming language.
CSS syntax refers to the way we write CSS code.
CSS is a simple, intuitive language that anyone can learn.

HTML VS CSS :
HTML is a markup language used to create static web pages and web applications.
CSS is a style sheet language responsible for the presentation of documents written in a markup language. 

Types of CSS :
1. Inline CSS -> Inline CSS has the highest priority.
2. Internal CSS.
3. External CSS.

Syntax :
p : is a selector
color : is a priority
red : is a value

p {
  color: red;
  text-align: center;
}

selectors :
tag selector : tag name -> p,h1,img,etc..
class selector : class name ->heading, myclass,etc..
id selector : id name -> myid, para, etc..

comment : 
/* This is a single-line comment */

/* This is
a multi-line
comment */
